item.title: Hey need help with anti leech
item.dc:creator: @sergiypro sergiypro
item.description:
@sergiypro wrote:

sigh, i thought you knew something. lets break you code down

java -Xmx512m -cp .;.(so far so good)
/jython.jar;.(not all servers use “jython.jar”)
/MySql/mysql-connector-java-3.0.08-ga-bin.jar server(i dont use mysql)

so no, your code doesnt work for all server.

it just works for your server.

almost every server has a diffrent run.bat

because due to the fact that coders are trying 2 prevent leachers, they try to rename files,

therefore most filenames are diffrent.

*sorry for spelling errors, 2 lazy
